# ciris-status takes NO environment variables.
#
# ciris-status is a ciris-server 0.5 node (the zero-env model): it boots from two
# CLI flags and resolves EVERYTHING else from signed CEG objects in its own
# corpus, authored by the OWNER at runtime. There is nothing to put in a .env.
#
#   Boot:   ciris-status --home /data --key-id ciris-status
#           (docker compose already passes these as `command:`)
#
# After the container is up, claim ownership and author config. The node prints a
# NodeCode + a one-time claim PIN on fresh boot; use the desktop client (or the
# raw API below) to claim, then author config:* and consent:replication peering.
#
# ── 1. Adapter config:* (probe targets, cadence, CORS) — POST /v1/config ──────
# All keys live under the `status.` namespace. A region/external provider is
# probed ONLY when its *_url is set; unset keys omit that component. See
# src/config.rs for the full key table. Examples (owner-authenticated):
#
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -H 'content-type: application/json' \
#     -d '{"key":"status.poll_secs","value":60}'
#
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.region.us.billing_url","value":"https://billing.us.example/"}'
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.region.us.proxy_url","value":"https://proxy.us.example/"}'
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.region.us.infra_url","value":"https://health.us.example/"}'
#
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.cors_origins","value":["https://ciris.ai","https://www.ciris.ai"]}'
#
#   # External search providers — KEYLESS by default (no billable call). Send the
#   # live key ONLY for a provider whose health endpoint is FREE:
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.external.exa.url","value":"https://api.exa.ai/health"}'
#   # opt into keyed (BILLABLE) probing per-provider — leave brave keyless:
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.external.exa.auth","value":true}'
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/config \
#     -d '{"key":"status.external.exa.api_key","value":"<key>"}'
#
# ── 2. consent:replication peering (Node A / the lens node) — POST /v1/federation/peering
# Peer with Node A so its `capacity:*` flows INTO this node's own corpus. This
# emits a DIRECTED consent grant + registers the peer's exported SignedKeyRecord;
# the runtime reconciler converges replication with no restart. Without it the
# node runs solo (self-attests health:liveness, empty roster).
#
#   curl -X POST https://status.ciris.ai/v1/federation/peering \
#     -d '{"peer_key_id":"ciris-server-steward","peer_key_record":{...}}'
#
# The full config:* / peering reference is DEPLOY.md.
